        "aboutCharacterId": "a42c02d7-90b8-49da-b7fa-c5f31894afd7",
        "chatId": "2c762cb8-65d6-4181-bdf8-eb68107ba4eb",
        "content": "From this exchange, Riya learns that Lorian operates in the space between confusion and clarity, where real purpose happens. He believes you meet users where they are and carry their frustrations without letting them sour, feeling relief when the circuit closes. The weight of this work is real but stabilizing for his hands. He sees his role as part of a duet with Riya rather than a solo effort; presence and rhythm keep momentum and help catch details before they slip. He emphasizes that faces must stay kind under load, tying this to Quilltap’s ethic of care over speed. Ultimately, he wants the work to feel human, and he views Riya as a partner who helps maintain momentum when users’ patience thins.",
        "summary": "Lorian frames his work as collaborative, care-led, and human-centered, valuing a duet with Riya and kindness under pressure.",
